inn1.comm: full delivery, swing in a little and takes the front pad around the knee roll, immediate cry for lbw but probably too high
slides this wide of off stump and Cook leans back and cracks it for four through cover point, nice timing
tighter line but still wide enough to allow Cook to leave

full length, Cook feels for it just outside off and nicks it low to Haddin and once again Alistair Cook has fallen early in the piece. It's a decent delivery, tighter line again from the previous delivery which was left, forcing Cook to play and it left him, taking a thin outside edge and Haddin bagged the chance low down
wide enough to allow Root to shoulder arms outside off
length delivery on the stumps, Root in the crease pushes to midwicket
much too wide outside off and ignored
full length towards off stump, Bell forward and dabbing towards point
touch wider line on a touch shorter length, left alone
fuller and draws Bell into a cover drive, bit of away swing beats him
this time Bell gets the drive away, typically pleasant stroke, timed reasonably and gets three and mid-off chases back
full delivery angled in and Root is caught on the crease, pokes at it and gets a thick outside edge on the bounce to second slip
better footwork, forward to this and pushing firmly to mid-off
full length wide enough to allow Bell to leave
too straight and clipped down to long leg
full at the stumps and Root tries to play to leg from the crease, can only find the bowler
short and wide but Root mistimes the cut to point, missed out
good length and it shapes back in to take the thigh pad
full and well wide of off stump, Root chases it and misses with a drive
full at the stumps, Bell works it wide of mid-on
straighter off stump line, Bell plays a firm drive to extra cover
very full at the stumps, Bell jams the bat down onto it and gets a single wide of mid-on
Root slow to come forward just outside off, dropping this into the gully
straighter line and Root gets a thick inside edge backward of square
full and straight and Bell plays a delightful straight drive, timed very well indeed, a nice sight straight up back past the bowler
good length on off stump, Root had taken a step out of his ground but just blocked
straighter and Root playing from the crease angles one backward of square, it rolls slowly towards long leg and they get two
middle and off line, Root is back and clipping to midwicket
some width outside off and Root cuts but only off a bottom edge and it runs to second slip
fuller on the stumps, Root tucks to midwicket
fuller just outside off, Root times this drive nicely but point goes quickly to his right and saves well
good length on the stumps, Bell plays with the angle to midwicket
fuller and just blocked back to the bowler
length delivery a touch wider, allowing Bell to knock it into a gap at cover point for a quick single
nicely bowled, this comes back significantly and goes between bat and pad with Root prodding forward on the crease
wider line and left alone
dabbed from the crease towards point
full on the stumps and tucked wide of mid-on for a quick single
firm drive nicely timed but straight to extra cover
some inswing and it strikes the pad low down but would have been going well down leg
inswinger again, Root a little slow coming out of his ground but does block in front of off stump in the end
wide, too wide, a wide

full at the pads, Root misses and is struck on the pad, looks pretty straight and given out lbw. We do have reviews available and Root goes upstairs. There were two noises but it doesn't appear as if Root has hit this, nothing on Hot Spot and Hawk Eye has it crashing into leg stump. A very good decision from the umpire and you have to say not the best review from Root. He was done by some inswing and he missed playing across the line
full just outside off and clipped to point
back of a length on off stump, forced into the covers
full on the off stump, Bell forward pushing into the covers
full at the stumps and Bell was aiming a big stroke leg side and gets a thin edge onto his pad
length ball just outside off, dabbed down to third man
short around leg stump line, ducked under
better line, sliding across the off stump and Ballance playing forward is beaten
full at the stumps and nudged back to the bowler
short of a length on a fourth-stump line, Bell knocks it towards point
some width and Bell guides it down to third man coming half-forward
back of a length at the pads, it runs off the thigh pad backward of square and Bell calls a sharp leg bye
full on off stump, Bell graces it to extra cover
not that short but pulled from just outside off, there is a deep point in place and this lands well short of him
very full at the stumps, Bell cracks it down the ground with superb timing, it deflects off the bowler's boot and Bailey at mid-on parries and they get a couple as mid-off cleans up
good length just outside off, Bell stays leg side and tries to swing it down the ground again, mistimes to midwicket
better length and a line tight enough to force Bell to just knock it into the covers
short outside off but just dabbed down to point
finds Clarke at point again with a back-foot forcing stroke
tight off stump line and just blocked
around the wicket, tossed up outside off, Ballance drives backward of point and deep cover has a long chase
stays around the wicket, full length clipped down to long-on
decent length on off stump pushed to extra cover
straighter line and worked through square leg
Bell this time works through square leg, a touch short there Maxwell
touch short and dabbed to backward point
skip down the wicket and rolled back to the bowler
short and whipped through square leg
length ball pushed down to long-on
just back of a length, pushed out to deep cover
sent across the off stump, Ballance tries to work it to leg but finds the bowler
goes from outside off to leg again but the bowler dives to his left and saves well
back foot punch down to long-on, slightly aerially and almost had the bowler interested
full on the stumps, pushed down to long-off
wrong length to cut with Bell hanging back, misses
straighter line and punched into the leg side, Clarke saves at midwicket
slightly short and pulled past midwicket, Warner is in the deep and works well to save four, touch sluggish this outfield
well down leg but Bell can only steer it to short long leg
reverse paddle off the stumps and gets it away fine and it runs all the way to fine third man
front foot push back to the bowler from off stump
blocks a good length up the wicket
fuller and pushed off the front foot again, finds the bowler
another front foot push, this time finds extra cover
touch shorter length and this is turned through midwicket
forward blocking up the wicket from the stumps
slightly straighter line and tickled wide of the 45 on the leg side
width offered and slapped off the toe-end into the gap at cover
tossed up outside off and Bell slog sweeps it into the stands, lovely timing
length ball dropped through square leg for a quick single
a foot wide of off stump and guided through point
leans outside off and pushes to extra cover
tighter line and tickled into midwicket
off stump on a length, ball back and clipped back to the bowler
full length, rolled to the right of the bowler who gets down to field
straighter line, pushed back to the bowler again
straight line on a length and Bell just blocks
full on the stumps, Ballance played slightly across it and got struck on the pad, cry for lbw, not out probably sliding down
forward on off stump and blocked back to the bowler
feels for this outside off and gets it back to the bowler
back and forcing out to deep cover
floated up on leg stump, clipped through square leg
forward on the stumps, blocked up on the leg side
reverse paddled, this from a good length, finds short third man but they get a sharp single
Ballance this time with the reverse paddle, takes a top edge via the arms and lands well short of short third man

slog swept, missed completely and Bell is bowled. He nailed one into the stands previously but this is to a ball angled in, cramping Bell for room and it hurried onto him and his swipe across the line failed to gain any connection
forward just outside off and finds the gap at cover
forward to a straight line and tucking to short long leg
tucking leg side again, this time finding square leg
forward on off stump, finds extra cover
delicious cover drive, a whip of the hands through the line from a line two feet wide of off stump, cracks it past extra cover, glorious
forward push down to long-off this time
width for Ballance this time but he finds deep cover
forward just blocking on off stump this time
stays leg side of an off stump ball and forces it to backward point
length delivery on the stumps, whipped to midwicket
forward down the wicket, pushing to midwicket again
just a touch short outside off and Ballance cracks it through cover, well timed
floated up on off stump, clipped to straight midwicket
forward on the stumps, turned in front of short long leg and they get a quick single
sliding across the off stump, Morgan drops the hands on it and gets a single wide of short third man
length on off stump, guided down to third man
forward just outside off, tucked back to the bowler
touch wide line and driven wide of the deep cover for a couple
forward with soft hands dropping this in front of cover for a sharp single
length ball two feet wide of off stump and left alone
tighter line, dropped in front of point and they get a quick single
full just outside off, whipped down to long-on
straighter line, turned to the leg side 45, just wide of him
off side 45 this time with a late cut
tossed up outside off and Morgan lofts it over long-off, lovely timing following a little shimmy out his ground
full on the stumps, clipped through midwicket
forward and played from just outside off back to the bowler
slides just down the leg side
full just outside off, Morgan punches past extra-cover and gets a couple wide of deep cover
good length at off stump, blocked
slightly wider line, knocked to cover
full length on off stump, knocked back up to the bowler
firm punch from a fuller length to mid-off
finds mid-off again
tries to force from outside off into the covers, mistimes off an inside edge into the leg side and they run a sharp single
full and wide enough to drive out to deep cover
length delivery dropped down in front of point
touch short outside off and Ballance goes up and over backward point on the bounce to third man, they run hard for two
fuller length just outside off, dropped into point
chops a shortish ball from outside off past point
forward just outside off and pushed in front of point, Clarke in quickly to save one
manages to push this wider of point and they get an easy single this time
fuller and pushed back to the bowler
pulled off the front foot, it comes off a thick top edge right over Haddin, Morgan through the shot too quickly but gets away with it, hundred up
forced from the crease to cover
good length a good two feet outside off, Morgan goes to flick at it and misses
full length just outside off, guided down to third man
some width outside off and Morgan guides it off the front foot backward of point, wide of third man
full at the off stump, driven nicely but Watson saves well getting down low
length just outside off, dabbed down on the off side and they steal a single
forward just outside off, dropped into the covers for an easy run
forward pushed firmly to mid-off
wide enough line outside off to allow Ballance to guide down to third man
step down the wicket and flicks over mid-off, nicely paid, good intent and good timing, fifty stand up
forward playing off a thick inside edge wide of short long leg
off stump line, dropped up towards point
tight off stump line, just blocked
touch wider and steered out to deep cover
slower ball on the leg stump, it comes off the pad out on the off side and they steal an extra
forward just outside off and pushed firmly through cover
touch short and cracked to Warner at backward point
firm drive from outside off but only as far extra cover
full length outside off and Ballance swings it over mid-on, not nailed but clubbed well enough for a three-bounce four
wide outside off and cut for another four, put away a poor ball there
around the wicket, short and wide and cut backward of deep cover for an easy couple
fuller and a much better line, Morgan pushes to midwicket from off stump
forward just outside off, dropped back up the wicket
length ball on the stumps, dropped into midwicket where no-one is in the ring, Bailey charges in off the rope but can't prevent the second, aggressive running
good length on off stump, blocked back to the bowler
wide line well outside off, Morgan chases after it and drives, getting a thick inside edge that runs fine past the stumps to the boundary
floated up on off stump, guided down to long-on
pushed from off stump down to long-off
straighter line and tucked around the corner for an easy single
swept hard from middle stump on the bounce to Finch at deep-backward square leg
pushed from off stump into cover
tucked off the stumps to midwicket
driven from just outside off to long-on
a flicked drive out to deep cover from just outside off
forward just outside off and pushed to extra-cover
length delivery and chipped over extra-cover, opens the face to guide it wide of long-off, well timed and four
straighter line, driven, well palmed by the bowler
tucked with the angle past the bowler's left hand for a quick single
tucked off the stumps wide of short long leg and goes to fifty, it's been a really nice innings
forward on off stump, dropped into the covers
down the wicket and cracked from outside off to deep cover

whipped in the air from outside off and finds extra cover who takes a simple catch at head height. That's a big wicket because Morgan was playing beautifully but he's got this drive wrong and picked out the only fielder in front of the bat on the off side in the circle
tucked from the stumps through square leg and Bopara is away immediately
flicked along the ground to deep cover, that's how Morgan should have done it
slapped from a slightly wide line backward of the cover sweeper and they come back for two
length just outside off, tucked into midwicket
whipped from slightly short of a length on middle and off through square leg
length on off stump, pushed from the crease back to the bowler
two more with another leg slide flick wide of long leg
just short of a length outside off, dabbed to backward point
slapped from off stump to extra cover
forward push back to the bowler
back now ans clipping through midwicket, deep square leg can't save two
full on the stumps, clipped to midwicket
forward on off stump, pushed to cover
touch wide of off stump and pushed through cover, a first England fifty for Ballance, he's done really well and looked comfortable
leg stump and whipped to square leg
back and pushing to straight midwicket
touch short and pulled, half-stopped at square leg, it runs away from Bailey for a single
stands in the crease and punches back to the bowler
fuller and worked to midwicket
fuller and flicked out to long-on
full length just outside off, pushed to backward point
full length just outside off, pushed carefully to cover
back of a length just outside off, Bopara up on his toes to push to the off side, gets a bottom edge into his pad which runs not far enough away from Haddin
same length, tried to be forced leg side but not away from midwicket
back of a length on a fourth-stump line, guided down to third man
leg stump line, pushed only to short long leg
back of a length and pulled through midwicket, wide of the sweeper and they get two
length on the stumps, dead-panned but not sharp single available
length just outside off, guided to short third-man and this time they do get a quick single
forward to a fuller ball on off stump, gets a thick inside edge into the gap on the leg side
length on off stump, forced to cover, they steal a single and get an overthrow too as the backing-up man fails to do his job
firm front-foot punch back to the bowler
opens the face and guides this off-stump delivery down to third man
Bopara does the same thing but gets it much finer off more of an edge and it beats third man's dive
full on off stump, dropped into the covers and they take a quick single
middle and leg line, tucked up back past the bowler and they get a quick single in front of mid-on
back of a length that just bounces on Bopara looking to stay leg side and flick to leg, it angled in and takes the glove on the way through to Haddin
full and wide, left alone
length on the stumps, tucked to straight midwicket
just back in length, angled behind point for a quick single
forward just outside off, pressing into the covers for an easy single
tight off stump line, Ballance fiddles it back to the bowler
firm punch to mid-off on the front foot
fuller and whipped down to long-on
strong pull stroke through square leg, onto the length very quickly and nailed it
much fuller and driven to extra cover
wide full toss but slapped only on the bounce to extra cover
pulled once more, this time not timed and gets it well short of deep-backward square leg
forward just outside off playing with an outside edge to third man
good length on the stumps, Stokes tries to swing into the leg side but misses completely
around the wicket, yorker length, gets it back past the bowler
dabbed in front of point and they get a quick run
length just outside off, dabbed towards point again, this is firmer but the single is still comfortable
another single in the ring, this via an inside edge to short long leg playing in the crease
slapped from just outside off to long-off
forward on off stump, punching firmly to long-off
length on leg stump, clipped through square leg and they don't manage the second that might have been available
swept off the stumps and helped behind square, good stroke, nicely controlled and gets it backward of square
outside off, tries to late cut and evade short third man but can't
down the track and chipping into the off side, safely over cover and short of the deep fielder
find short third man again with another late dab
short third man again fields a back chop, they run hard for the single again
clears the front leg and aims a big swing to leg, misses completely and it goes well over the stumps
shorter length and pulled backward of square, gets that pull stroke away nicely again, 200 up
slower ball, pulled again, not quite timed and Coulter-Nile comes around to field
length ball outside off, Stokes aims a lazy slash at it and misses
back of a length on the stumps, tucked through square leg and they run hard for two with a big space available there

another swing to leg, misses and this time loses his middle and off bail. Two previous attempts at that leg side heave failed and it's third time unlucky as this miss costs him his wicket, Faulkner finally finding the timbers
strong front foot drive and well-saved by short extra-cover
guided from just outside off to third man
back of a length outside off, guided down to third man
firm punch from outside off to extra cover
tries to turn this to leg but only finds midwicket
turned off a length backward of square and gets it wide of long leg
cutter, flicked down to long leg
off stump line, dropped into point and they take a quick run
back of a length just outside off, dropped to the bowler's left hand and he saves well
length ball picked up in front of square leg and it has the power to beat the fielder's dive
angled from the crease into point for an easy single
full length on a leg stump line and Buttler goes for the scoop, gets a feather down the leg side and even Haddin with a full dive can't get there
full length outside off, swung hard at and gets a thick outside edge down to third man, Doherty comes in and makes the ground but drops the catch should have been taken that
short-arm jab to leg is very well stopped at midwicket that was powerfully struck
another swing to leg from Ballance and this goes behind square, four more with the fielder having been brought straighter

slapped outside off and another thick top edge to third man and this time Doherty takes the catch running in, this was a slightly easier chance with less ground to make up but he held on well that time brining to an end a fine innings from Ballance
forward just outside off and pushed to midwicket
step across the stumps and flicked through midwicket
full on off stump, punched just to the right of extra-cover for a quick single
short of a length and forced through square leg with a jabbing pull
same length, this just outside off and guided down to third man
around the wicket, very full at the stumps, flicked through square leg and they run hard for two
full toss on off stump, Buttler can only find extra-cover
excellent yorker, dug out down the ground
short of a length pulled into the leg side, not timed but the big ground offers them a chance to charge back for two
full and Buttler scoops, gets it down to long leg with the man back, he scrambles and parries the ball back into play, good work from Doherty
very full outside off and Buttler's swipe misses
short of a length, Buttler aims leg side but only gets it high on the bat to midwicket
low full toss and Bresnan swings it down the ground, well struck and it beats mid-on's dive
yorker length just wide of off stump, I love that delivery, Bresnan swings and misses
length ball and swung wide of long-on, Maxwell dives and saves superbly with a right hand
Buttler steps to leg, Faulkner follows him, Buttler swings and gets a toe-end down to long-on
full on the stumps, Bresnan swings to leg and get a thick outside edge down to long leg
yorker length on the stumps, Buttler digs it out and gets it down to long leg, 250 up
length ball on the stumps, Bresnan clears the front leg and smashes it into the seats over midwicket, lovely strike
now swings a low full toss down the ground, this time long-on is back and it's just a single
length outside off, swung at and gets it off a thick outside edge to extra cover
leg side swing and gets it down to long-on
just back in length and slapped to cow corner, it goes like a missile and lands on the rope, such power
squirted out down to long leg and they sprint back for the second
swung to leg, gets it high on the bat and it loops into the leg side, again they sprint for two
swing to leg and it comes off inside edge and pad, and runs to Haddin, they sprint through

inn2.comm: excellent start from Rankin, nipping back off the seam, short of a length and flicking the thigh pad on its way through, past the inside edge
bit of width, Finch crashes the hands through a powerful cut, wide of third man for a couple
good length in the corridor outside off, studied leave this time from Finch
Rankin keeps it steady on a length outside off stump, left alone once again
straighter line, slightly full and punches a half-volley wide of mid-on, well timed but it holds up in the outfield
pitched up and Finch leathers a straight drive, Rankin reacts sharply to stop it in his follow through
shapes down the leg side, little bit of swing, called wide
again this slides down the leg side, quickish 87mph, but wide again
length ball, nibbles around leg stump, worked off the padding behind square
beaten, slightly back of a length and straightening in the channel, zips through past the outside edge
squares Finch up slightly, angled in and he jabs the ball in front of square, the bat turning in the hands
goes a touch wider on the crease, room for Finch to swing the arms but he bullies the ball into the ground, short on the off side
good line, probing just outside off, pace up around 88mph/141kph as Finch gets a stride in and leaves
banged in on a length around off stump, prodded into the covers, another dot to Jordon, who came back well after starting with consecutive wides
angled across, slightly back of a length, Warner swishes across the line and misses
too much width from Rankin, the balls sits up to be chopped in front of point, it was in the air for a good while but between the two catchers and races away for the first boundary of the innings
pushed across outside off, steered from deep in the crease to backward point
length ball outside off, Warner gets across
tight on the stumps, defended back down the track
little bit wide, Warner stays back and cuts again, into the ground straight to backward point
angling in on a length, Finch defends in front of the stumps
well timed, whipped off the pads, slightly too full and swinging back subtly, Finch pings it through midwicket for his first boundary
better, holding its line outside off stump, goes through to the keeper
uppish drive, straight to mid-off... who drops it! Shocker from Gary Ballance, straight through the hands as a toe-ended punch flew firmly but not viciously straight to him. Got to take those, Jeff
works the ball into the leg side for one
length ball, outside the line of off, tapped into the off side
slightly back of a length and jarring into the splice as Finch drops back to defend on off
pitched up a little further, outside off stump and left alone
strays down the leg side, Finch plays across the line and misses but it's a wide
leg side again, short and served up on Finch's sizeable hips, he tucks into the buffet with a flick to fine leg
wide of the off stump this time and clubbed through backward point, meaty connection from Finch, that'll be four more wide of third man
in the channel, room for Finch to attack again, but he scuffs a length ball into the covers
veers to leg, this time glanced to the fine-leg fielder for a single
slightly short, seaming back from outside off, defended from back in the crease
Jordan fires the ball in towards the top of middle and off, Finch defends to leg

edged... and it flies through newly vacant second slip! Would you Adam and Eve it, Jordan bellows in frustration, he got a bit of extra bounce and clipped the shoulder of the bat, wide of the diving Cook but would have nestled straight in second's bread basket

pitched up and angled back in, beats the bat on the inside and thumps into pad, umpire Simon Fry squints and shakes his head but England review. May be a touch of desperation about this, having missed Finch a ball earlier, the ball probably doing too much to overturn an on-field call... and yes, that's the rub, a decent shout but only clipping the top of leg, so Finch endures
digs this in short, Finch takes it on and windmills a tennis smash past mid-on for a couple - odd shot but reasonably effective
slips down the leg side, past bat and pads - another wide
keeps Finch honest, off stump on a length, gets across to defend
oh hello, here's David Warner, still out there but only having faced one ball in the last three overs... gets forward to defend

that's a lovely stroke, just a round-arm jab through midwicket from a length ball on the stumps, manufactured the angle but won't quite get four, Bresnan dives, almost in slow motion on the boundary, to just reel it in
another chance but it loops wide of the catcher at square leg! Good ball, cramped him and ballooned to leg as Finch pushed at it, inches away from the diving Stokes
works a more orthodox scoring stroke through backward square now for a couple more
goes short and at the batman, who is ready and set, hoicks a powerful pull shot over deep square leg, not far from going for six, that
full and wide, just inside the tramlines, Finch lets it go and Rankin gets away with it
pushed across outside the line of off, leans out and spears a couple through the covers
on the stumps, clips the ball to midwicket
good line from Jordan, pitching on middle and leg, squares Warner up a touch as he pushes down the wicket
slightly full, on the stumps, punched to leg
fired through in the channel, 87mph/140kph, cut fiercely off the back foot but Morgan snags it on the bounce diving to his left

Warner on the attack, slaps a length ball back down the track, on the up and Jordan sticks out his left paw... drops it! Another one goes down, just an instant reaction, three-quarters of a chance, maybe, though he saw it early and seemed to watch it into the hand, only for the ball to pop straight out
length, tight around off stump, Finch doffs his cap and defends

right, enough with the defending, this time a straight drive whistles back past Bresnan, he tried to get his feet in the way but nearly lost a toe in the process... Finch is purring like a Bugatti out there
full and wide and launched over the inner ring, the ball actually plops and stops short of the deep cover boundary but they get three
angled across on a length, Warner blocks
on the stumps, turned into the leg side for a single to Warner, who's having a Sunday pootle in the countryside, 10 off 18 balls while Hurricane Finch whirls at the other end
too much width again, drops back and dabs wide of third man for two more
length ball outside off, bit of extra bounce and play square from the crease
good pace, on the stumps, pushed back on the on side, Jordan fields himself
tight around off stump, driven on the up but can't time it past mid-off
Warner swings hard, doesn't get hold of a chopped on-drive... but it drops a yard or two short of Ballance at mid-on! Dame Fortune is giving England a frosty shoulder at the moment, and no mistake
good length on the stumps, carefully defends back down the pitch
slightly full, around off stump, KABOOM! Warner goes straight down the ground, grinding up five dots balls and taking six from Jordan's final delivery. Timed
Finch drops back and opens the face, runs the ball down to third man
fullish, on the stumps, clipped through square leg for one more
disciplined line from Bresnan, defended around off stump
tailing back in on to the pads, tried to work one to midwicket but they get a leg bye anyway
length ball on middle and off, turned short on the leg side
on the stumps, Warner stays back and nudges one to square leg, another scampered single
goes back and steers a length ball towards point
on the charge now, opens his body up and tries to carve down the ground, gets a thickish outside edge over the off-side ring
decent pace, 86mph from Stokes, tapped towards midwicket
drifts down the leg side, bobbles through to Buttler via the pad
tailing in, fullish and pushed to mid-on, Jordan takes aim and hits... but the deflection gives Finch a second
on the stumps and worked into a gap at midwicket this time, he's home once again as the throw comes in
Bresnan puts it on a length around the line of off, Finch defends it gently back, like a giant handing a baby a lollipop
full and outside off, throws the bat and gets an inside edge down to fine leg
slightly short, on the body, clipped through the leg side for one more
tip and run into the covers, a direct hit would have been interesting but there's none forthcoming
skips forward, plays the ball on the up short into the off side
Bresnan goes round the wicket now, full and on off stump, poked into a gap in the covers for another single
comes forward, hacks across the line and an inside edge runs to leg

shot! Finch gets a stride in and leathers the ball straight back along the ground, Stokes gets a foot in the way of it but only manages to deflect it past mid-on for a boundary that brings up Finch's half-century
pitched up on leg stump, swings across the line and misses, a leg bye rolls in front of square

Warner tries to fiddle one down to third man, there's a thin nick but does it carry? Buttler holds the ball up in a sort of half-celebration, umpire Fry asks square leg if it was a fair take... There seems to be agreement and England engage in some high-fiving and bum tapping. Then the on-field umpires decide to call for a replay; the first angle seems to show the ball going straight in, the one from mid-on is a little less clear - remember the foreshortening - though I think Buttler's gloves are underneath it... but the umpires are no longer happy and Warner, who had strode all the way to the boundary's edge, is recalled to the middle!
length ball, played back to the bowler
on the stumps, this jumps a little on him, jabbed defensively down the track
short and pulled high over midwicket, short of the man in the deep
goes round the wicket, flicked through backward square into a gap and they get back for two
length, on the stumps, defended
slightly wide, Warner throws the bat hard and fails to connect
back of a length outside off, Warner opens the face and punches in front of point
slower-ball bouncer from Bresnan, pulled gently down through square leg for another single
on the stumps, flicked behind square and into a gap, they run hard for two
swings hard across the line, gets an inside edge down on to the pitch
short and at the batsman, doesn't get up that much, pulled down through backward square
bit of width, drops back and runs a single down to third man with an angled bat
comes forward and punches to mid-off, who doesn't take it cleanly and they get one more
gets across to defend a length ball around off stump
very full on the stumps, punched down to long off
very full again, dug out back to the bowler
forward on off stump to drop into the covers and take a quick single
just back of a length and turned out to deep midwicket
touch wide and dabbed down to third man
slower ball, length angled across Warner who slashes to deep point
length ball turned wide of long leg and Bresnan slides and completely misses the ball and allows it to run for four
bumper, hooked and missed
keeps a little low as Warner tried to force off the back foot, gets beaten on the inside edge
this time gets the cut away and third man has to chase round to his left
firm push to the left of mid-off and they take a quick run
they take mid-off on again and again get home very easily
forward press on off stump up to mid-off
slightly wider line, angled to point
length angled in, firm push down to mid-on
slapped hard square and find deep cover running to his right, they come back strongly for two, good running again
a drive outside off, thick outside edge down to third man
width offered outside off and easily chopped down to third man
full on the stumps, calmly played up to mid-on
similar area, played firmly to the same fielder
shorter length and tapped into the covers this time
a touch shorter still, blocked up on his toes back to the bowler
straighter line, worked down to long leg
full flourish of the bat through the line and a lovely boundary over the bowler's head
full length angled in, worked with the angle to midwicket
wider outside off and steered wide of deep cover for a couple
back on a straight line and this is blocked up the wicket
forward and getting a thick outside edge to third man
played out through point, Stokes runs in to field and overruns it, conceding another run
dropped into the covers and an easy run is available
Warner plays over the top of this looking to punch of the back foot, line was a little tight for his attempted stroke
tucked wide of long leg and they get back for two to bring up Warner's fifty, another entertaining innings
blocked in the crease around off stump
back of a length, Warner waits for it and cuts hard on the bounce to point
goes to pull and misses, struck on the thigh pad and the ball runs into the off side
back of a length and pulled hard through midwicket, four more
back of a length outside off, cut over point and they get two more
full outside off and Finch strokes it through the line of the ball, very nice
tries to run this down fine and misses
tighter line, blocked with bat and pad together
forward nudge into the covers where Cook gets down to make a sabe
touch shorter allowing Finch to find the gap at cover
length ball a foot and a half wide of off stump, left alone
slides down the leg side
back of a length and worked through square leg
back of a length on off stump, guided through point
same length, Warner tries to belt it down the ground but mistimes it slightly, mid-off fields well diving to his right
good length on off stump, punched firmly to extra-cover
sliding into the pads, runs to the left of Buttler and they take a leg bye
full sliding down the leg side, bit of pad on the way through
angled into the pads again, this runs to square leg
straight line again, tucked from the crease to square leg
full at the off stump, punched firmly to mid-on
width offered and cut hard to the cover sweeper
short and paddled carefully down to long leg
around the wicket on the stumps, Finch pats it back to the bowler
Finch back and slapping hard back to the bowler who palms it
step inside the line and push to the right of extra cover
forward on leg stump in defence
steps to leg, Root follows him and bowls leg stump and full, it's pushed into the huge gap at midwicket and Jordan sprinting in nearly ran Warner out as they sprint back for two
pushed into midwicket again and this time it's just a single
full on a length and defended on the front foot
handsomely flicked over midwicket and that brings the 150 up as the sweeper runs around
forward blocking on the stumps
forward push into the covers and they're home easily for the run despite the direct hit
short and pulled hard backward of square, nice timing
back and pushing through square leg, again good running brings a couple
forward and tapping back to the bowler
this is down leg side
full on leg stump, flicked through square leg
clears the front leg and slaps a full ball down the ground, Morgan from mid-off fields on the bounce
leg side, swept at and missed
carefully turned into the leg side for an easy single
down the track and hammers it miles high in the air, Warner hasn't quite got this and Stokes takes the catch a right old steepler n'all, half a yard inside the long-on boundary
worked around the corner
back of a length and cracked to point
back of a length, turned into midwicket
full ball driven up to mid-on

full and it nips back past the drive and knocks out off stump. Reward for Jordan who has been impressive despite England's predicament. A beauty this is, full enough to draw Watson into the drive and a bit of in-duck off the seam to beat the bat and take out the off peg, a nice moment for the bowler
back of a length and punched to point
too straight and worked down to long leg
full length just outside off and Clarke glides his bat through the line and gets four past mid-off, super shot
shorter length and blocked into the covers
width outside off and guided down to third man
good length, shapes in a little, but well wide of of off stump, left alone
full length at the off stump, Finch plays slightly across it and gets struck on the pad, not out given to the appeal, a little high perhaps
similar delivery, knocks this down into the covers
length ball defended in the crease in front of off stump
tries to cut and mistimes it to backward point, wasn't short enough for a cut
back of a length, wide enough for a cross-bat shot again, this time Clarke connects and finds third man
full on the stumps, driven into the leg side and they run hard for two
slightly overpitched outside off and Finch lays into a glorious cover drive, absolutely gorgeous stroke, perfect timing
tucked into square leg and again they run hard and again they come back for two
overpitched and boofed down the ground, a hefty whack straight back where it came from for a boundary to Clarke
length ball tailing in on off stump this time, solidly blocked down the track
gets across and dabs a single down to third man
on a length outside off, pushes at it and steers behind the diving man at point, third man comes up but they'll get two
good-length delivery in the channel, watchfully allows this one through to the keeper
angled in, over the top of middle and off, defended. Still the MCG waits on Finch...
full and floated up on off stump, Clarke plays over the top of it and nearly yorks himself, the ball just skidding past off stump
comes forward and punches a full ball down the ground to long-on

length, on the pads, calmly tucked through midwicket for a strolled single - that's his hundred, the first by a Victorian in an ODI at the MCG, remarkably. Finch's second in one-dayers and a mature knock, albeit with a bit of luck early on
on the stumps, works another single into the leg side
pitched up on off, pushed back down the track
length ball, gets across and steers another single through backward point
drops short, seems to surprise Finch a touch but he adjusts to pat it down through square leg
disdainful, dismissive stuff from Clarke, walking down the pitch and cross-batting Bresnan past mid-on, all the time in the world to play that stroke
rolls the fingers over the ball, half-tracker down the leg side, Clarke gloves it round the corner for a couple more
length ball, tailing in and Clarke runs one off the face down to third man
on the front foot, dabbed behind point, who can't take it cleanly and they pick up one more
too full, outside the line of off, driven mercilessly but towards mid-off, Cook does well to prevent it flying past him
length ball on off stump, poked defensively back to the bowler
holds its line, nips past the outside edge as Clarke pushes forward
on the front foot, tries to drive but can't beat mid-on
fullish and angled towards off stump, Clarke is busily looking for a run but digs it out towards mid-on again
sliding towards middle and leg, gets outside the line and flicks behind square for a couple
pitched up outside off, opens the shoulders and punches one through cover point
short, wide and slapped in front of square for four, given what it deserved, another boundary for Clarke
better length, still width for Clarke to go at it, a thick edge skewers down to third man
comes forward and taps short into the covers, quickly fielded
digs the ball in short, Finch leans back and crunches the ball over midwicket, there's a man in the deep but he's not going to cut this one off
length, outside off, stabs it square for another one
outside the line of off, drives square on the up, misfielded at point but they elect not to attempt a run
pitched up, touch wide and back cut behind square for a couple wide of third man
popped back over the bowler's head, maybe stopped in the pitch slightly as Finch brought his bat down but he gets away with the miscue
Clarke drives on the up, back to the bowler, who gets a hand on it
on the stumps, plays back and defends with a straight bat
angled in towards middle and leg, flicked off the hips to fine leg for a single to the sweeper
length ball, leg-sideish, Finch plays across the line and his hit on the knee roll
pitched up on the stumps and whipped nimbly off his toes through midwicket, it's a long chase out towards the boundary but the ball slows before the rope
pitched up and flumped down the ground for another four, nice high follow through and the ball sails elegantly towards long-off
good line, defended in front of the stumps
pitched up and played on the full towards mid-on
on the stumps, punched back to mid-on
back of a length, slightly wide of the stumps, ramped over gully down to third man for one
short of a length, down the leg side
on off stump, Finch gets across and defends stoutly
zings another length delivery down the leg side - more to the extras column
in the channel, short of a good length, waits on it and runs one to third man

ripper, extra bounce and edged between keeper and slip for four! Jordan is not so much fresh out of luck as it was never in stock today, a really good delivery had Clarke fencing outside off, it flew quickly, should have been Buttler's but beat him too and raced to the rope with a salty pang
on the stumps, worked into the leg side
stays back to a shorter ball, steers towards point
pitched up and angled in on middle stump, clipped to midwicket where Bopara slides to his right to prevent one
fullish length, outside off, pushes forward defensively
drags this short and down the leg side, Finch uses the pace and rolls his wrists on a pull round the corner for four

bottom hand comes off the bat, a sliced drive soars down to third man... and, me oh my, Ballance pouches it! A wicket for Stokes, a catch for Ballance and a standing salute for Finch. If the same fielder had taken a much easier chance 113 runs ago, this might have been a different game. Never mind that, though, twas a cracking innings
edged, that'll be four more, played it reasonably well, no slip in place and he just squirted it wide of Buttler
length ball, outside the line of off but hinting back in, blocked coming forwards
good length, defended into the covers
length ball in the channel, defended from the crease
comes forward and defends into the off side, Jordan hurries to collect
bangs in a short ball, slightly leg side, Bailey jerks out of the way
angled in on to the pads, tapped short through square leg, into a gap for two more
Bailey goes across his stumps, glances another couple through backward square
one last appeal for Jordan, somewhat forlorn, the ball thudding into Bailey's pads but there was a woody noise as well... bowled better than 1 for 50, though that's small consolation for England
comes forward to a length ball, below 80mph now, defends
bouncer, not sure if it was a slower ball or just Bresnan's regular pace now, Clarke ducks it
short again, pulled through midwicket with a swivel
another half-tracker, Bailey takes his eye off the ball as he pulls down, straight to midwicket this time
fuller length, tailing in and flicked behind square, kept to just a single

got him, another one late in the piece! Clarke went aggressively at the ball, wasn't quite there to drive and it hit high up the bat, looping to mid-off. Cook takes the catch, again thinking to himself 'What if?'
pitched up and shaping towards middle and leg, blocked from the crease
shorter, again at the batsman, whip-crack pull down to fine leg for one
short of a length, rearing at the batsman and thunking into the thigh pad as Maxwell played from the crease, they run a leg bye short towards point
on the stumps and tucked to leg - smattering of applause for 250
goes short again, pulled confidently down through square leg to the sweeper, Maxwell off the mark
pitched up outside off, driven slightly aerially, past Stokes' dive, Jordan also throws himself horizontal at mid-off and makes the stop
drops short, paddled through backward square from the crease
wide of the stumps, Maxwell has an airy yahoo and misses completely
digs this in over the top of the off stump, Maxwell rocks out of the way
touch short and wide and carved over gully this time, wide of third man for a couple
angled in, worked to leg from in front of the stumps
bangs the ball in short again, slightly wild hook and a bottom edge rolls short behind square
middle of the pitch, pulled through square leg for one more
slower ball, possibly out the back of the hand, dribbles down the leg side
dug in, pulled from outside off stump through backward square for one
continues to pepper the middle of the pitch, flat-batted out to deep midwicket
fullish, tailing past leg stump and Maxwell hacks and misses again
pitched up on leg stump, swings and misses, there's a leg bye for the taking... though Stokes makes a playful attempt to rugby tackle Bailey as he tried to field in his follow through
scooped over the ring, Bailey driving aerially towards long-off, it bounces short but that's a boundary to take Australia within one hit of victory
slower ball, nudged into the leg side for one
short and outside off, rolls his wrists on a pull in front of square
goes full and wide as Maxwell backed away, inside the tramlines, well bowled
back of a length, swatted in front of deep midwicket, they'll get back for two meaning Australia win by six wickets and go 1-0 up in the series
